3c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 &#124; \u0395\u039b\u039b\u0391\u0394\u0391|trans-title=Coronavirus: In quarantine at Piraeus the cruiser 'El. Venizelos' with the 20 cases|date=31 March 2020|website=iefimerida.gr}}</ref>\n\n=== April ===\n\n*On 1 April, 101 new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the country total to 1415. One more death from coronavirus was reported, bringing the country death toll to 50.<ref name=\"cnn213658\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/213658/koronoios-live-oi-anakoinoseis-tsiodra-xardalia|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: 50 \u03bf\u03b9 \u03bd\u03b5\u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03af \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u03c7\u03ce\u03c1\u03b1 \u03bc\u03b1\u03c2 - 1.415 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1|last=Newsroom|date=2020-04-01|website=cnn.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n*On 2 April, 129 new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the country total to 1544. 27 new cases were reported in the general population, 23 in the Ritsona refugee and immigrant camp, and 79 new cases on the ship El. Venizelos which is being kept off the port of [[Piraeus]], bringing the total cases on the ship to 119. Three more deaths from coronavirus were reported, bringing the country death toll to 53.<ref name=\"ethnos97808\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.ethnos.gr/ygeia/97808_koronoios-53-thanatoi-sti-hora-mas-91-sti-meth-1544-synolika-ta-kroysmata|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: 53 \u03b8\u03ac\u03bd\u03b1\u03c4\u03bf\u03b9 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u03c7\u03ce\u03c1\u03b1 \u03bc\u03b1\u03c2, 91 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u039c\u0395\u0398, 1.544 \u03c3\u03c5\u03bd\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac \u03c4\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1|last=Newsroom|date=2020-04-02|website=ethnos.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n*On 3 April, it was announced that the total number of confirmed cases in the country was 1613. Six more deaths from coronavirus were reported, bringing the country death toll to 59.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.in.gr/2020/04/03/greece/koronaios-deite-tin-enimerosi-apo-s-tsiodra-kai-n-xardalia-2/|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03b1\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2 : 99 \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 \u2013 \u03a3\u03c4\u03b1 1.613 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c5\u03bd\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac \u2013 59 \u03b8\u03ac\u03bd\u03b1\u03c4\u03bf\u03b9 |last=Newsroom|date=2020-04-03|website=in.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n*On 4 April, 60 new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the country total to 1673. Nine more deaths from coronavirus were reported, bringing the country death toll to 68. 92 coronavirus patients were being treated in intensive care units.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/214043/live-koronoios-h-enimerosi-apo-tsiodra-xardalia-gia-tin-pandimia|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u03a3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 68 \u03bf\u03b9 \u03bd\u03b5\u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03af \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u03c7\u03ce\u03c1\u03b1 \u03bc\u03b1\u03c2 - 1.673 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1|last=Newsroom|date=2020-04-04|website=cnn.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n*On 5 April, 62 new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the country total to 1735. Five more deaths from coronavirus were reported, bringing the country death toll to 73. 93 coronavirus patients were being treated in intensive care units.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/214130/koronoios-stoys-73-oi-nekroi-sti-xora-mas-1-735-ta-kroysmata|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u03a3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 73 \u03bf\u03b9 \u03bd\u03b5\u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03af \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u03c7\u03ce\u03c1\u03b1 \u03bc\u03b1\u03c2 - 1.735 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 |last=Newsroom|date=2020-04-05|website=cnn.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n*On 6 April, 20 new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the country total to 1755. Six more deaths from coronavirus were reported, bringing the country death toll to 79.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/214252/koronoios-live-oi-anakoinoseis-tsiodra-xardalia|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u03a3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 79 \u03bf\u03b9 \u03bd\u03b5\u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03af \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u03c7\u03ce\u03c1\u03b1\u03c2 \u03bc\u03b1\u03c2 - 1.755 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03b5\u03c0\u03b9\u03b2\u03b5\u03b2\u03b1\u03b9\u03c9\u03bc\u03ad\u03bd\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1|last=Newsroom|date=2020-04-06|website=CNN.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n*On 7 April, 77 new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the country total to 1832. Two more deaths from coronavirus were reported, bringing the country death toll to 81.<ref name=\":23\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/214398/koronoios-live-oi-anakoinoseis-tsiodra-xardalia|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: 81 \u03bd\u03b5\u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03af \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 1.832 \u03b5\u03c0\u03b9\u03b2\u03b5\u03b2\u03b1\u03b9\u03c9\u03bc\u03ad\u03bd\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u03c7\u03ce\u03c1\u03b1 \u03bc\u03b1\u03c2|last=Newsroom|date=2020-04-07|website=CNN.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n*On 8 April, 52 new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the country total to 1884. Two more deaths from coronavirus were reported, bringing the country death toll to 83. The number of coronavirus patients in ICUs was 84.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://eody.gov.gr/0408_briefing_covid19/|title=\u0395\u03bd\u03b7\u03bc\u03ad\u03c1\u03c9\u03c3\u03b7 \u03b4\u03b9\u03b1\u03c0\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03b5\u03c5\u03bc\u03ad\u03bd\u03c9\u03bd \u03c3\u03c5\u03bd\u03c4\u03b1\u03ba\u03c4\u03ce\u03bd \u03c5\u03b3\