3ad\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 - \u03a3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 73 \u03bf\u03b9 \u03b1\u03c3\u03b8\u03b5\u03bd\u03b5\u03af\u03c2 \u03c0\u03bf\u03c5 \u03bd\u03bf\u03c3\u03bf\u03cd\u03bd|date=8 March 2020|website=ieidiseis|language=el|access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref> and starting on 10 March, all educational institutions were closed for 14 days.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.minedu.gov.gr/news/44308-10-03-20-prosorini-apagorefsi-tis-ekpaideftikis-leitourgias-olon-ton-ekpaideftikon-domon|title=\u03a5\u03a0\u039f\u03a5\u03a1\u0393\u0395\u0399\u039f \u03a0\u0391\u0399\u0394\u0395\u0399\u0391\u03a3 & \u0398\u03a1\u0397\u03a3\u039a\u0395\u03a5\u039c\u0391\u03a4\u03a9\u039d - 10-03-20 \u03a0\u03c1\u03bf\u03c3\u03c9\u03c1\u03b9\u03bd\u03ae \u03b1\u03c0\u03b1\u03b3\u03cc\u03c1\u03b5\u03c5\u03c3\u03b7 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u03b5\u03ba\u03c0\u03b1\u03b9\u03b4\u03b5\u03c5\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae\u03c2 \u03bb\u03b5\u03b9\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c1\u03b3\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03cc\u03bb\u03c9\u03bd \u03c4\u03c9\u03bd \u03b5\u03ba\u03c0\u03b1\u03b9\u03b4\u03b5\u03c5\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ce\u03bd \u03b4\u03bf\u03bc\u03ce\u03bd|date=10 March 2020|website=\u03a5\u03c0\u03bf\u03c5\u03c1\u03b3\u03b5\u03af\u03bf \u03a0\u03b1\u03b9\u03b4\u03b5\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u0398\u03c1\u03b7\u03c3\u03ba\u03b5\u03c5\u03bc\u03ac\u03c4\u03c9\u03bd|language=el|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 March two villages in Western Macedonia, [[Damaskinia]] and [[Dragasia]], were quarantined after several cases among their residents were confirmed. Movement in and out of the villages was banned, allowing only medical staff and municipal staff to supply medication and food.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ethnos.gr/ellada/94293_koronoios-se-karantina-ta-horia-damaskinia-kai-dragasia|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u03a3\u03b5 \u03ba\u03b1\u03c1\u03b1\u03bd\u03c4\u03af\u03bd\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03c7\u03c9\u03c1\u03b9\u03ac \u0394\u03b1\u03bc\u03b1\u03c3\u03ba\u03b7\u03bd\u03b9\u03ac \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u0394\u03c1\u03b1\u03b3\u03b1\u03c3\u03b9\u03ac|last=|first=|date=2020-03-16|website=\u0388\u03b8\u03bd\u03bf\u03c2|language=el|trans-title=Coronavirus: The villages of Damaskinia and Dragasia are quarantined|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> On 18 March, Greece announced new coronavirus restrictions pertaining to migrant camps. For thirty days, the movement of camp residents would be restricted to small groups between 7am and 7pm, which could only include one person per family and would be controlled by police on public transport. Specialised medical teams were sent to the camps for the creation of virus isolation areas and compulsory temperature checking. All other visits to the camps whether by individuals or organisations were suspended for at least 14 days.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/world/greece-unveils-new-coronavirus-restrictions-in-migrant-camps-12553024|title=Greece unveils new coronavirus restrictions in migrant camps|date=March 18, 2020|agency=Channel New Asia}}</ref> On the same day, Deputy Minister of Civil Protection and Crisis Management Nikos Hardalias announced a ban on public gatherings of 10 or more people and the imposition of a 1,000 euro fine on violators.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news247.gr/koinonia/koronoios-se-ischy-i-apagoreysi-synathroiseon-ano-ton-10-atomon-oi-apodektes-metakiniseis.7605395.html|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u03a3\u03b5 \u03b9\u03c3\u03c7\u03cd \u03b7 \u03b1\u03c0\u03b1\u03b3\u03cc\u03c1\u03b5\u03c5\u03c3\u03b7 \u03c3\u03c5\u03bd\u03b1\u03b8\u03c1\u03bf\u03af\u03c3\u03b5\u03c9\u03bd \u03ac\u03bd\u03c9 \u03c4\u03c9\u03bd 10 \u03b1\u03c4\u03cc\u03bc\u03c9\u03bd - \u039f\u03b9 \u03b1\u03c0\u03bf\u03b4\u03b5\u03ba\u03c4\u03ad\u03c2 \u03bc\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03ba\u03b9\u03bd\u03ae\u03c3\u03b5\u03b9\u03c2|last=|first=|date=|website=www.news247.gr|language=el|trans-title=Coronavirus: Ban on public gatherings of 10 or more people - Acceptable movements|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-greece-idUSKBN2152YH|title=Greece bans gatherings of 10 people and more, effective Thursday|date=2020-03-19|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-03-21|language=en}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 March, [[Ministry of Maritime Affairs and Insular Policy (Greece)|Minister of Maritime Affairs and Insular Policy]] Giannis Plakiotakis announced that only permanent residents and supply trucks would be allowed to travel to the Greek islands, with effect from 6am local time on 21 March. Travellers need to provide proof of permanent residence (via a tax certificate) on the island to which they wish to travel. People who are already on the islands and wish to leave are allowed to return to the mainland.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.ethnos.gr/oikonomia/94785_koronoios-ta-metra-gia-ergazomenoys-ki-epiheiriseis|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u03a4\u03b1 \u03bc\u03ad\u03c4\u03c1\u03b1 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03b5\u03c1\u03b3\u03b1\u03b6\u03cc\u03bc\u03b5\u03bd\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b9 \u03b5\u03c0\u03b9\u03c7\u03b5\u03b9\u03c1\u03ae\u03c3\u03b5\u03b9\u03c2|last=|first=|date=2020-03-18|website=\u0388\u03b8\u03bd\u03bf\u03c2|language=el|trans-title=Coronavirus: Measures for Workers and Businesses|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ekathimerini.com/250865/article/ekathimerini/news/government-bans-travel-to-the-islands-for-non-residents|title=Government bans travel to the islands for non-residents {{!}} Kathimerini|website=www.ekathimerini.com|language=English|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 March, the Greek government announced a ban on all nonessential transport and movement across the country, starting from 6 a.m on 23 March until 6 April. Movement is permitted only for a prescribed set of reasons that include moving to or from the workplace during normal business hours, shopping for food or medicine, visiting a doctor or assisting a person in need of help, exercising individually or in pairs or walking a pet, attending a ceremony (wedding, baptism, funeral etc.), and cases of divorced parents moving to ensure communication with their children. People returning to their permanent places of residence will also be exempt. Citizens leaving their home are required to carry their ID or passport with them, as well as some type of certification explaining the reason for their movement which has to be confirmed by their employer or by themselves. The options include filling in a special form that can be downloaded from the government website forma.gov.gr, sending a free SMS to the number 13033, or explaining their reason in a signed handwritten declaration. The information needed include the name, home address, time of departure from home, and the specific reason for transport that falls under one of the exceptions. Members of the government and parliament as well as all Health, Civil Protection, Law Enforcement and Armed Forces personnel were excluded from the measure. The [[Hellenic Police]], the [[Municipal Police (Greece)|Municipal Police]], the [[Hellenic Coast Guard]] and the National Transparency Authority are required to enforce the restrictions and issue fines of 150 euros for each offense.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iefimerida.gr/ellada/apagoreysi-kykloforias-pos-tha-pate-deytera-doyleia|title=\u0391\u03c0\u03b1\u03b3\u03cc\u03c1\u03b5\u03c5\u03c3\u03b7 \u03ba\u03c5\u03ba\u03bb\u03bf\u03c6\u03bf\u03c1\u03af\u03b1\u03c2: \u03a0\u03ce\u03c2 \u03b8\u03b1 \u03c0\u03ac\u03c4\u03b5 \u03c4\u03b7 \u0394\u03b5\u03c5\u03c4\u03ad\u03c1\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u03b4\u03bf\u03c5\u03bb\u03b5\u03b9\u03ac -\u03a0\u03bf\u03cd \u03b5\u03c0\u03b9\u03c4\u03c1\u03ad\u03c0\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03b9 \u03b7 \u03bc\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03ba\u03af\u03bd\u03b7\u03c3\u03b7 {{!}} \u0395\u039b\u039b\u0391\u0394\u0391|last=IEFIMERIDA.GR|first=NEWSROOM|date=2020-03-22|website=iefimerida.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://forma.gov.gr/|title=Instructions to the public|last=|first=|date=|website=forma.gov.gr|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.in.gr/2020/03/22/english-edition/greece-quarantine-mitsotakis-declares-nationwide-lockdown-6am-tomorrow/|title=Greece in quarantine: Mitsotakis declares nationwide lockdown as of 6am tomorrow|last=in.gr|date=2020-03-22|website=in.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ekathimerini.com/250917/article/ekathimerini/news/pm-announces-full-lockdown-in-bid-to-curb-coronavirus-spread|title=PM announces full lockdown in bid to curb coronavirus spread {{!}} Kathimerini|website=www.ekathimerini.com|language=English|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> On the same day, it was also announced that daytime public transport services will be limited, although ensuring sufficient service during business hours. Journeys by car are only permitted for the specific exemptions, and the driver may only have one passenger in the vehicle.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.in.gr/2020/03/22/greece/apagoreysi-kykloforias-analytikos-odigos-pou-tha-epitrepetai-metakinisi-ti-tha-isxysei-gia-tous-ergazomenous/|title=\u0391\u03c0\u03b1\u03b3\u03cc\u03c1\u03b5\u03c5\u03c3\u03b7 \u03ba\u03c5\u03ba\u03bb\u03bf\u03c6\u03bf\u03c1\u03af\u03b1\u03c2: \u0391\u03bd\u03b1\u03bb\u03c5\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc\u03c2 \u03bf\u03b4\u03b7\u03b3\u03cc\u03c2 - \u03a0\u03bf\u03cd \u03b8\u03b1 \u03b5\u03c0\u03b9\u03c4\u03c1\u03ad\u03c0\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03b9 \u03b7 \u03bc\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03ba\u03af\u03bd\u03b7\u03c3\u03b7 -\u03a4\u03b9 \u03b8\u03b1 \u03b9\u03c3\u03c7\u03cd\u03c3\u03b5\u03b9 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 \u03b5\u03c1\u03b3\u03b1\u03b6\u03bf\u03bc\u03ad\u03bd\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2|last=in.gr|date=2020-03-22|website=in.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> Since the beginning of the curfew through 6 April, Greek police have recorded more than 20,000 violations (increasing in recent days) and made 348 arrests of offenders.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Constantine|first1=Alex|url=https://greekcitytimes.com/2020/04/06/greece-records-more-than-20000-violations-since-covid-19-imposed-curfew/|title=Greece records more than 20,000 violations since COVID-19 imposed curfew|date=6 April 2020|work=Greek City Times|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> On 4 April the measure was extended until 27 April.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.civilprotection.gr/ru/node/6251|title=\u0395\u03bd\u03b7\u03bc\u03ad\u03c1\u03c9\u03c3\u03b7 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u03a5\u03c6\u03c5\u03c0\u03bf\u03c5\u03c1\u03b3\u03cc \u03a0\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae\u03c2 \u03a0\u03c1\u03bf\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03c3\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u0394\u03b9\u03b1\u03c7\u03b5\u03af\u03c1\u03b9\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2 \u039a\u03c1\u03af\u03c3\u03b5\u03c9\u03bd \u039d\u03af\u03ba\u03bf \u03a7\u03b1\u03c1\u03b4\u03b1\u03bb\u03b9\u03ac \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u03b5\u03ba\u03c0\u03c1\u03cc\u03c3\u03c9\u03c0\u03bf \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u03a5\u03c0\u03bf\u03c5\u03c1\u03b3\u03b5\u03af\u03bf\u03c5 \u03a5\u03b3\u03b5\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c4\u03bf \u03bd\u03ad\u03bf \u03ba\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc, \u039a\u03b1\u03b8\u03b7\u03b3\u03b7\u03c4\u03ae \u03a3\u03c9\u03c4\u03ae\u03c1\u03b7 \u03a4\u03c3\u03b9\u03cc\u03b4\u03c1\u03b1|last=generalsecretary|date=2020-04-04|website=\u0393\u03b5\u03bd\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae \u0393\u03c1\u03b1\u03bc\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b5\u03af\u03b1 \u03a0\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae\u03c2 \u03a0\u03c1\u03bf\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03c3\u03af\u03b1\u03c2|language=el|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 March, Deputy Minister for Civil Protection and Crisis Management Nikos Hardalias announced additional restrictive measures for a duration of 14 days in the [[Municipalities and communities of Greece|municipalities]] of [[Kastoria]], [[Orestida]] and [[Nestorio]] of [[Kastoria (regional unit)|Kastoria Regional Unit]] as well as those of [[Xanthi]] and [[Myki, Greece|Myki]] of [[Xanthi (regional unit)|Xanthi Regional Unit]]. A night curfew was imposed from 8:00 p.m. until 8:00 a.m. the following morning and some options of the lockdown movement permits were suspended. Only close relatives can attend a funeral and pet owners are allowed to walk their pet for up to 15 minutes and near their house only.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.civilprotection.gr/el/simantika-themata/prostheta-perioristika-metra-gia-ti-metakinisi-ton-politon-stoys-dimoys-xanthis|title=\u03a0\u03c1\u03cc\u03c3\u03b8\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c0\u03b5\u03c1\u03b9\u03bf\u03c1\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac \u03bc\u03ad\u03c4\u03c1\u03b1 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b7 \u03bc\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03ba\u03af\u03bd\u03b7\u03c3\u03b7 \u03c4\u03c9\u03bd \u03c0\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03c4\u03ce\u03bd \u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 \u0394\u03ae\u03bc\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 \u039e\u03ac\u03bd\u03b8\u03b7\u03c2, \u039c\u03cd\u03ba\u03b7\u03c2, \u039a\u03b1\u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c1\u03b9\u03ac\u03c2, \u039f\u03c1\u03b5\u03c3\u03c4\u03af\u03b4\u03bf\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u039d\u03b5\u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c1\u03af\u03bf\u03c5 \u03bb\u03cc\u03b3\u03c9 \u03ba\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03bf\u03cd COVID-19|last=generalsecretary|date=2020-03-31|website=\u0393\u03b5\u03bd\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae \u0393\u03c1\u03b1\u03bc\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b5\u03af\u03b1 \u03a0\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae\u03c2 \u03a0\u03c1\u03bf\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03c3\u03af\u03b1\u03c2|language=el|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\nOn 2 April, following the confirmation of a case in [[Mykonos]], all construction activities on the island were suspended.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.civilprotection.gr/ru/node/6247|title=\u0395\u03bd\u03b7\u03bc\u03ad\u03c1\u03c9\u03c3\u03b7 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u03a5\u03c6\u03c5\u03c0\u03bf\u03c5\u03c1\u03b3\u03cc \u03a0\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae\u03c2 \u03a0\u03c1\u03bf\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03c3\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u0394\u03b9\u03b1\u03c7\u03b5\u03af\u03c1\u03b9\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2 \u039a\u03c1\u03af\u03c3\u03b5\u03c9\u03bd \u039d\u03af\u03ba\u03bf \u03a7\u03b1\u03c1\u03b4\u03b1\u03bb\u03b9\u03ac \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u03b5\u03ba\u03c0\u03c1\u03cc\u03c3\u03c9\u03c0\u03bf \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u03a5\u03c0\u03bf\u03c5\u03c1\u03b3\u03b5\u03af\u03bf\u03c5 \u03a5\u03b3\u03b5\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c4\u03bf \u03bd\u03ad\u03bf \u03ba\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc, \u039a\u03b1\u03b8\u03b7\u03b3\u03b7\u03c4\u03ae \u03a3\u03c9\u03c4\u03ae\u03c1\u03b7 \u03a4\u03c3\u03b9\u03cc\u03b4\u03c1\u03b1|last=generalsecretary|date=2020-04-02|website=\u0393\u03b5\u03bd\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae \u0393\u03c1\u03b1\u03bc\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b5\u03af\u03b1 \u03a0\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae\u03c2 \u03a0\u03c1\u03bf\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03c3\u03af\u03b1\u03c2|language=el|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref> On 5 April, another case was confirmed and a night curfew was imposed from 8:00 p.m. until 8:00 a.m. the following morning while some options of the lockdown movement permits were suspended for 14 days.<ref name=\":24\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.civilprotection.gr/ru/node/6252|title=\u03a0\u03c1\u03cc\u03c3\u03b8\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c0\u03b5\u03c1\u03b9\u03bf\u03c1\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac \u03bc\u03ad\u03c4\u03c1\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u039c\u03cd\u03ba\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u03a3\u03b1\u03bd\u03c4\u03bf\u03c1\u03af\u03bd\u03b7 \u03bb\u03cc\u03b3\u03c9 \u03ba\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03bf\u03cd COVID-19|last=generalsecretary|date=2020-04-05|website=\u0393\u03b5\u03bd\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae \u0393\u03c1\u03b1\u03bc\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b5\u03af\u03b1 \u03a0\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae\u03c2 \u03a0\u03c1\u03bf\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03c3\u03af\u03b1\u03c2|language=el|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref> The same day all construction activity was suspended for 30 days on the island of [[Santorini]], although no cases have been reported there.<ref name=\":24\" />\n\nFrom 8 April, the Hellenic Police installed permanent roadblocks and intensified checks of vehicles in all [[Highways in Greece|national roads and highways]] across the country, as well of travellers at the airports, ports, railway and bus stations. Anyone travelling by car without a valid reason to a destination other than his permanent residency is charged with a fine of 300 euros, is obliged to return to his place of origin and the vehicle registration plates are seized for 60 days.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.civilprotection.gr/el/enimerosi-apo-ton-yfypoyrgo-politikis-prostasias-kai-diaheirisis-kriseon-niko-hardalia-kai-ton-12|title=\u0395\u03bd\u03b7\u03bc\u03ad\u03c1\u03c9\u03c3\u03b7 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u03a5\u03c6\u03c5\u03c0\u03bf\u03c5\u03c1\u03b3\u03cc \u03a0\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae\u03c2 \u03a0\u03c1\u03bf\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03c3\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u0394\u03b9\u03b1\u03c7\u03b5\u03af\u03c1\u03b9\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2 \u039a\u03c1\u03af\u03c3\u03b5\u03c9\u03bd \u039d\u03af\u03ba\u03bf \u03a7\u03b1\u03c1\u03b4\u03b1\u03bb\u03b9\u03ac \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u03b5\u03ba\u03c0\u03c1\u03cc\u03c3\u03c9\u03c0\u03bf \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u03a5\u03c0\u03bf\u03c5\u03c1\u03b3\u03b5\u03af\u03bf\u03c5 \u03a5\u03b3\u03b5\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c4\u03bf \u03bd\u03ad\u03bf \u03ba\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc, \u039a\u03b1\u03b8\u03b7\u03b3\u03b7\u03c4\u03ae \u03a3\u03c9\u03c4\u03ae\u03c1\u03b7 \u03a4\u03c3\u03b9\u03cc\u03b4\u03c1\u03b1|last=generalsecretary|date=2020-04-08|website=\u0393\u03b5\u03bd\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae \u0393\u03c1\u03b1\u03bc\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b5\u03af\u03b1 \u03a0\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae\u03c2 \u03a0\u03c1\u03bf\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03c3\u03af\u03b1\u03c2|language=el|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n\n==== Travel restrictions abroad ====\nOn 9 March, the [[Hellenic Civil Aviation Authority]] announced the temporary suspension of all flights to and from [[northern Italy]], affecting all Greek airports and all airlines.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ekathimerini.com/250404/article/ekathimerini/news/all-flights-to-and-from-northern-italy-suspended|title=All flights to and from northern Italy suspended {{!}} Kathimerini|website=www.ekathimerini.com|language=English|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> On 14 March the suspension was extended to all passenger flights to and from Italy, excluding cargo and sanitary ones.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-greece-death/greece-reports-two-more-coronavirus-fatalities-suspends-all-flights-to-italy-idUSKBN2110H1|title=Greece reports two more coronavirus fatalities, bans all flights to Italy|date=March 14, 2020|agency=Reuters}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 March Greece closed its borders with [[Albania]] and [[North Macedonia]], deciding to suspend all road, sea and air links with these countries, while only permitting the transportation of goods and the entry of Greek nationals and residents. The suspension of ferry services to and from [[Italy]], air links to [[Spain]], as well as the prohibition of all cruise ships and sailboats docking in Greek ports was also decided.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news247.gr/politiki/koronoios-ektakta-metra-kleinoyn-ta-synora-me-alvania-kai-v-makedonia-tilefonima-mitsotaki-se-ieronymo.7602425.html|title=\u0395\u03ba\u03c4\u03b1\u03ba\u03c4\u03b1 \u03bc\u03ad\u03c4\u03c1\u03b1 - \u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u039a\u03bb\u03b5\u03af\u03bd\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd \u03c4\u03b1 \u03c3\u03cd\u03bd\u03bf\u03c1\u03b1 \u03bc\u03b5 \u0391\u03bb\u03b2\u03b1\u03bd\u03af\u03b1 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u0392. \u039c\u03b1\u03ba\u03b5\u03b4\u03bf\u03bd\u03af\u03b1 - \u03a0\u03b1\u03c1\u03ad\u03bc\u03b2\u03b1\u03c3\u03b7 \u039c\u03b7\u03c4\u03c3\u03bf\u03c4\u03ac\u03ba\u03b7 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b9\u03c2 \u03b5\u03ba\u03ba\u03bb\u03b7\u03c3\u03af\u03b5\u03c2|website=www.news247.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref> The same day it was announced that a 14-day home restriction will be mandatory for those who enter the country.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news247.gr/koinonia/koronoios-kleinoyn-ta-emporika-katastimata-se-karantina-osoi-erchontai-apo-exoteriko.7603146.html|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u039a\u03bb\u03b5\u03af\u03bd\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd \u03c4\u03b1 \u03b5\u03bc\u03c0\u03bf\u03c1\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac \u03ba\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1\u03c3\u03c4\u03ae\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 - \u03a3\u03b5 \u03ba\u03b1\u03c1\u03b1\u03bd\u03c4\u03af\u03bd\u03b1 \u03cc\u03c3\u03bf\u03b9 \u03ad\u03c1\u03c7\u03bf\u03bd\u03c4\u03b1\u03b9 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03b5\u03be\u03c9\u03c4\u03b5\u03c1\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc|website=www.news247.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 March, Greece and the other EU member states decided to close their external borders to all non-EU nationals. In Greece, the entry of citizens of countries from outside the European Union is only permitted for a condition that relates exclusively to an emergency or family matter. All private pleasure boats from abroad were also banned from entering the country.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iefimerida.gr/kosmos/koronoios-i-ee-kleinei-ta-synora-karantina-ellada|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u0397 \u0395\u0395 \u03ba\u03bb\u03b5\u03af\u03bd\u03b5\u03b9 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03c3\u03cd\u03bd\u03bf\u03c1\u03b1 -\u03a0\u03bf\u03b9\u03bf\u03b9 \u03c4\u03b1\u03be\u03b9\u03b4\u03b9\u03ce\u03c4\u03b5\u03c2 \u03b8\u03b1 \u03bc\u03c0\u03b1\u03af\u03bd\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd \u03c3\u03b5 \u03ba\u03b1\u03c1\u03b1\u03bd\u03c4\u03af\u03bd\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1 {{!}} \u039a\u039f\u03a3\u039c\u039f\u03a3|last=IEFIMERIDA.GR|first=NEWSROOM|date=2020-03-18|website=iefimerida.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> On 19 March, Turkey closed the land border crossings with Greece at [[Karaa\u011fa\u00e7, Edirne|Karaa\u011fa\u00e7]] and [[\u0130psala|Ipsala]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ethnos.gr/kosmos/94854_koronoios-i-toyrkia-kleinei-ta-synora-me-tin-ellada-kai-ti-boylgaria|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u0397 \u03a4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c1\u03ba\u03af\u03b1 \u03ba\u03bb\u03b5\u03af\u03bd\u03b5\u03b9 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03c3\u03cd\u03bd\u03bf\u03c1\u03b1 \u03bc\u03b5 \u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03c4\u03b7 \u0392\u03bf\u03c5\u03bb\u03b3\u03b1\u03c1\u03af\u03b1|date=2020-03-18|website=\u0388\u03b8\u03bd\u03bf\u03c2|language=el|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\nFrom 23 March, Greece suspended all passenger flights from the UK as well as all sea, rail and road connections with Turkey, with an exception for Greek citizens and those who have residence permits or whose main residence is in Greece, as well as trucks and ships that transport goods.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/212372/koronoios-telos-apo-ta-mesanyxta-oi-ptiseis-apo-vretania-kai-toyrkia|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u03a4\u03ad\u03bb\u03bf\u03c2 \u03bf\u03b9 \u03c0\u03c4\u03ae\u03c3\u03b5\u03b9\u03c2 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u0392\u03c1\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03bd\u03af\u03b1 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03a4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c1\u03ba\u03af\u03b1|last=Newsroom|date=2020-03-23|website=CNN.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\n=== Economic measures ===\nOn 18 March, in a joint news conference, [[Ministry of Finance (Greece)|Finance Minister]] [[Christos Staikouras]], Labour Minister [[Giannis Vroutsis|Yannis Vroutsis]], and Development & Investments Minister [[Adonis Georgiadis]] announced a package of measures to support the economy, businesses and employees. The measures include the suspension, for four months, of tax and social security obligations of corporations that were ordered to close by the state decree, with the sole condition that they do not dismiss any workers. This measure covers about 220,000 businesses and 600,000 employees. The measures also include an \u20ac800 stipend as well as a four-month suspension of payment of March taxes on employees of businesses the activity of which was suspended and on freelance professionals who work in sectors affected by the pandemic. The reduction of VAT tax from 24% to 6% on pharmaceutical products such as gloves, masks and antiseptics was also announced. Moreover, the Finance Minister  announced the inclusion of Greece in an emergency assets purchases\u2019 program worth 750 billion euros launched by the [[European Central Bank]], and also stated the 3.5% primary surplus target for Greece is no longer in effect, according to a [[Eurogroup]] decision.<ref name=\":3\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tanea.gr/2020/03/18/english-edition/greece-takes-sweeping-measures-to-protect-business-labour-from-coronavirus-tempest/|title=Greece takes sweeping measures to protect business, labour from coronavirus tempest|last=Team|first=TANEA|date=2020-03-18|website=\u03a4\u0391 \u039d\u0395\u0391|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ekathimerini.com/250809/article/ekathimerini/business/greece-says-ecb-emergency-package-makes-12-billion-euro-in-debt-eligible|title=Greece says ECB emergency package makes 12 billion euro in debt eligible {{!}} Kathimerini|website=www.ekathimerini.com|language=English|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 March, [[Prime Minister of Greece|Prime Minister]] [[Kyriakos Mitsotakis]], in a nationally televised address, announced the revision of the [[Government budget|State Budget]] to allocate more than 10 billion euros in support of the economy. The suspension of tax and social security obligations of corporations and the number of beneficiaries of the \u20ac800 stipend was extended to include all businesses harmed by the pandemic, all freelancers and self-employed workers and the majority of private sector workers. The state will also cover the cost of beneficiaries\u2019 insurance, pension, and health payments. The PM also stated that the Easter bonus would be paid in full to all employees and announced a special bonus for health and civil protection workers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newsbomb.gr/politikh/story/1064307/koronoios-mitsotakis-to-doro-pasxa-tha-katavlithei-kanonika-aytoi-tha-lavoyn-800-eyro|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2 - \"\u03a4\u03b5\u03bb\u03b5\u03c3\u03af\u03b3\u03c1\u03b1\u03c6\u03bf\" \u039c\u03b7\u03c4\u03c3\u03bf\u03c4\u03ac\u03ba\u03b7: \u0391\u03bd \u03c7\u03c1\u03b5\u03b9\u03b1\u03c3\u03c4\u03b5\u03af \u03b8\u03b1 \u03c0\u03ac\u03c1\u03c9 \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 \u03bc\u03ad\u03c4\u03c1\u03b1 \u03c0\u03b5\u03c1\u03b9\u03bf\u03c1\u03b9\u03c3\u03bc\u03bf\u03cd \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u03ba\u03c5\u03ba\u03bb\u03bf\u03c6\u03bf\u03c1\u03af\u03b1\u03c2|last=Newsroom|date=|website=Newsbomb|language=el|trans-title=Coronavirus - Mitsotakis: If needed I'll take new restriction measures|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ekathimerini.com/250836/article/ekathimerini/news/greek-pm-announces-more-financial-aid-bonus-for-health-workers|title=Greek PM announces more financial aid, bonus for health workers {{!}} Kathimerini|website=www.ekathimerini.com|language=English|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n\n=== Suspension of businesses and workplaces ===\nOn 12 March, a two-week closure of all theatres, courthouses, cinemas, gyms, playgrounds and clubs was announced.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tanea.gr/2020/03/12/greece/ektakta-metra-kleinoun-kinimatografoi-theatra-kai-kentra-diaskedasis/|title=\u0395\u03ba\u03c4\u03b1\u03ba\u03c4\u03b1 \u03bc\u03ad\u03c4\u03c1\u03b1: \u039a\u03bb\u03b5\u03af\u03bd\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd \u03ba\u03b9\u03bd\u03b7\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03bf\u03b3\u03c1\u03ac\u03c6\u03bf\u03b9, \u03b8\u03ad\u03b1\u03c4\u03c1\u03b1 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03ba\u03ad\u03bd\u03c4\u03c1\u03b1 \u03b4\u03b9\u03b1\u03c3\u03ba\u03ad\u03b4\u03b1\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2|date=12 March 2020|website=tanea.gr|language=el|access-date=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 March, the nationwide closure of all shopping centres, cafes, restaurants, bars, museums and archaeological sites and food outlets, excluding supermarkets, pharmacies and food outlets that offer take-away and delivery only, was announced.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ekathimerini.com/250618/article/ekathimerini/news/malls-cafes-bars-eateries-to-close-as-coronavirus-cases-rise-to-190|title=Malls, cafes, bars, eateries to close as coronavirus cases rise to 190|date=13 March 2020|website=ekathimerini.com|language=en|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref> On 14 March, all organised beaches and ski resorts were closed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ethnos.gr/politiki/93995_koronoios-kleinoyn-paralies-kai-hionodromika-me-entoli-mitsotaki|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u039a\u03bb\u03b5\u03af\u03bd\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd \u03c0\u03b1\u03c1\u03b1\u03bb\u03af\u03b5\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03c7\u03b9\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03b4\u03c1\u03bf\u03bc\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac \u03bc\u03b5 \u03b5\u03bd\u03c4\u03bf\u03bb\u03ae \u039c\u03b7\u03c4\u03c3\u03bf\u03c4\u03ac\u03ba\u03b7|date=2020-03-14|website=\u0388\u03b8\u03bd\u03bf\u03c2|language=el|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 March, the government announced the closure of all hotels across the country, from midnight on March 22 and until the end of April. Only hotels that accommodate personnel that guard the border will continue to operate, as well as three hotels in Athens and Thessaloniki and one hotel per [[Regional units of Greece|regional unit]] will remain open. Moreover, all Greek citizens returning from abroad will be subjected to mandatory surveillance and isolation for at least 14 days.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/211904/koronoios-kleinoyn-kai-ta-xenodoxeia|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u039a\u03bb\u03b5\u03af\u03bd\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03be\u03b5\u03bd\u03bf\u03b4\u03bf\u03c7\u03b5\u03af\u03b1|last=Newsroom|date=2020-03-19|website=CNN.gr|language=el|trans-title=Coronavirus: Hotels are also closed|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.ert.gr/hotels-are-closing-greeks-returning-from-abroad-will-be-put-under-quarantine/|title=Hotels are closing- Greeks returning from abroad will be put under quarantine|last=Tsirigotaki|first=Eve|date=2020-03-19|website=ERT International|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> On 22 March, all parks, recreation areas and marinas were also closed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.in.gr/2020/03/22/greece/apagoreysi-kykloforias-analytikos-odigos-pou-tha-epitrepetai-metakinisi-ti-tha-isxysei-gia-tous-ergazomenous/|title=\u0391\u03c0\u03b1\u03b3\u03cc\u03c1\u03b5\u03c5\u03c3\u03b7 \u03ba\u03c5\u03ba\u03bb\u03bf\u03c6\u03bf\u03c1\u03af\u03b1\u03c2: \u0391\u03bd\u03b1\u03bb\u03c5\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc\u03c2 \u03bf\u03b4\u03b7\u03b3\u03cc\u03c2 - \u03a0\u03bf\u03cd \u03b8\u03b1 \u03b5\u03c0\u03b9\u03c4\u03c1\u03ad\u03c0\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03b9 \u03b7 \u03bc\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03ba\u03af\u03bd\u03b7\u03c3\u03b7 -\u03a4\u03b9 \u03b8\u03b1 \u03b9\u03c3\u03c7\u03cd\u03c3\u03b5\u03b9 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 \u03b5\u03c1\u03b3\u03b1\u03b6\u03bf\u03bc\u03ad\u03bd\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2|last=in.gr|date=2020-03-22|website=in.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n\n=== Closure of educational institutions ===\nStarting on 28 February, with four confirmed cases in the country, the precautionary local closure of schools was decided when there was concern that members of these school communities may have come into contact with a coronavirus carrier. On the same day, all educational trips abroad programmed by Greek schools were suspended and various municipalities around the country began disinfecting schools locally.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ert.gr/eidiseis/ellada/kinonia/koronoios-ichnilateitai-i-poreia-ton-nosoynton-metra-profylaxis-anastellontai-ta-episkeptiria/|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u0399\u03c7\u03bd\u03b7\u03bb\u03b1\u03c4\u03b5\u03af\u03c4\u03b1\u03b9 \u03b7 \u03c0\u03bf\u03c1\u03b5\u03af\u03b1 \u03c4\u03c9\u03bd \u03bd\u03bf\u03c3\u03bf\u03cd\u03bd\u03c4\u03c9\u03bd-\u039c\u03ad\u03c4\u03c1\u03b1 \u03c0\u03c1\u03bf\u03c6\u03cd\u03bb\u03b1\u03be\u03b7\u03c2-\u0391\u03bd\u03b1\u03c3\u03c4\u03ad\u03bb\u03bb\u03bf\u03bd\u03c4\u03b1\u03b9 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03b5\u03c0\u03b9\u03c3\u03ba\u03b5\u03c0\u03c4\u03ae\u03c1\u03b9\u03b1 (video)|last=\u03a0\u03b1\u03c0\u03b1\u03ca\u03c9\u03ac\u03bd\u03bd\u03bf\u03c5|first=\u0397-\u0392|date=2020-02-28|website=ert.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ieidiseis.gr/ellada/item/36949-koronoios-pote-tha-apofasistoyn-ta-kleista-sxoleia-stin-ellada|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u03a0\u03cc\u03c4\u03b5 \u03b8\u03b1 \u03b1\u03c0\u03bf\u03c6\u03b1\u03c3\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03cd\u03bd \u03c4\u03b1 \u03ba\u03bb\u03b5\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03ac \u03c3\u03c7\u03bf\u03bb\u03b5\u03af\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1|last=iEidiseis|website=www.ieidiseis.gr|language=el-gr|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ieidiseis.gr/ellada/item/36906-koronoios-stin-ellada-proliptikes-apolymanseis-se-dimosia-ktiria-apo-ton-dimo-iliou|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1: \u03a0\u03c1\u03bf\u03bb\u03b7\u03c0\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ad\u03c2 \u03b1\u03c0\u03bf\u03bb\u03c5\u03bc\u03ac\u03bd\u03c3\u03b5\u03b9\u03c2 \u03c3\u03b5 \u03b4\u03b7\u03bc\u03cc\u03c3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c4\u03ae\u03c1\u03b9\u03b1 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u0394\u03ae\u03bc\u03bf \u0399\u03bb\u03af\u03bf\u03c5|last=iEidiseis|website=www.ieidiseis.gr|language=el-gr|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> On 4 March, the closure of all public and private educational institutions of all levels in [[Elis (regional unit)|Ilia]], [[Achaea]] and [[Zakynthos]] was decided<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ieidiseis.gr/ellada/item/37222-koronoios-stin-ellada-ektakta-metra-anakoinonei-i-kyvernisi|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1: \u03a4\u03b1 \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 \u03ad\u03ba\u03c4\u03b1\u03ba\u03c4\u03b1 \u03bc\u03ad\u03c4\u03c1\u03b1|last=iEidiseis|website=www.ieidiseis.gr|language=el-gr|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> and from 8 March all educational trips within the country were suspended.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nOn 10 March, the operation of all schools, universities, daycare centres and all other educational establishments were suspended nationwide for fourteen days.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kathimerini.gr/1068505/article/epikairothta/ellada/kleinoyn-gia-dyo-evdomades-sxoleia-panepisthmia-paidikoi-sta8moi-kai-frontisthria|title=\u039a\u03bb\u03b5\u03af\u03bd\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03b4\u03cd\u03bf \u03b5\u03b2\u03b4\u03bf\u03bc\u03ac\u03b4\u03b5\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c7\u03bf\u03bb\u03b5\u03af\u03b1, \u03c0\u03b1\u03bd\u03b5\u03c0\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03ae\u03bc\u03b9\u03b1, \u03c0\u03b1\u03b9\u03b4\u03b9\u03ba\u03bf\u03af \u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03b8\u03bc\u03bf\u03af \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03c6\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03c4\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03ae\u03c1\u03b9\u03b1 {{!}} Kathimerini|website=www.kathimerini.gr|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> A special purpose leave of 15 days was introduced for working parents.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news247.gr/politiki/koronoios-ektakta-metra-adeia-eidikoy-skopoy-stoys-goneis.7599804.html|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2 - \u03ad\u03ba\u03c4\u03b1\u03ba\u03c4\u03b1 \u03bc\u03ad\u03c4\u03c1\u03b1: \u0386\u03b4\u03b5\u03b9\u03b1 \u03b5\u03b9\u03b4\u03b9\u03ba\u03bf\u03cd \u03c3\u03ba\u03bf\u03c0\u03bf\u03cd \u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 \u03b3\u03bf\u03bd\u03b5\u03af\u03c2|website=www.news247.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> Ten days later, on 20 March, the closure period was extended such that all educational institutions would remain closed until 10 April.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.alfavita.gr/ekpaideysi/316080_kleista-eos-tis-10-aprilioy-sholeia-kai-panepistimia|title=\u039a\u03bb\u03b5\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03ac \u03ad\u03c9\u03c2 \u03c4\u03b9\u03c2 10 \u0391\u03c0\u03c1\u03b9\u03bb\u03af\u03bf\u03c5 \u03c3\u03c7\u03bf\u03bb\u03b5\u03af\u03b1 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03c0\u03b1\u03bd\u03b5\u03c0\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03ae\u03bc\u03b9\u03b1|website=Alfavita|language=el|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n=== Suspension of religious services ===\nOn 9 March 2020, the Standing Holy [[Synod]] of the [[Church of Greece]], the country's established [[Eastern Orthodox Church]], discussed the coronavirus epidemic and issued an [[encyclical]] that was sent to the dioceses of the Church of Greece. Having stated that the [[Holy Communion]] could by no means be a way of transmission of diseases, the Standing Synod decided to continue offering and receiving the [[Holy Communion]].<ref name=\"kathimcommunion\">{{cite web | title=\u0399\u03b5\u03c1\u03ac \u03a3\u03cd\u03bd\u03bf\u03b4\u03bf\u03c2: \u039f \u03ba\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2 \u03b4\u03b5\u03bd \u03bc\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03b4\u03af\u03b4\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03b9 \u03bc\u03b5 \u03c4\u03b7 \u0398\u03b5\u03af\u03b1 \u039a\u03bf\u03b9\u03bd\u03c9\u03bd\u03af\u03b1| website=[[Kathimerini|kathimerini.gr]] | date=9 March 2020 | url=https://www.kathimerini.gr/1068264/article/epikairothta/ellada/iera-synodos-o-korwnoios-den-metadidetai-me-th-8eia-koinwnia| access-date=3 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"orthtimescommunion\">{{cite web | title=Holy Synod of Church of Greece: We continue to receive the Holy Communion (upd) | website=OrthodoxTimes | date=9 March 2020 | url=https://orthodoxtimes.com/holy-synod-of-church-of-greece-we-continue-to-receive-the-holy-communion/ | access-date=3 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Reuters9March\">{{cite web | title=In era of coronavirus, Greek church says Holy Communion will carry on | website=[[Reuters]] | date=9 March 2020 | url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-greece-church-idUSKBN20W2N1 | access-date=10 March 2020}}</ref> The Synod's decision sparked controversy.<ref name=VOA>{{cite news|url=https://www.voanews.com/science-health/coronavirus-outbreak/coronavirus-sparks-church-state-controversy-greece|title=Coronavirus Sparks Church-State Controversy in Greece |author=Anthee Carasava|agency=Voice of America|date=9 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Straights/> The Synod's stance prompted criticism from the opposition [[Syriza]] party, with former [[Prime Minister|prime minister]] [[Alexis Tsipras]] criticising the hierarchy, as did former health minister [[Pavlos Polakis]].<ref name=Straights>{{cite news|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/coronavirus-bug-sparks-holy-communion-row-in-greece|title=Coronavirus: Bug sparks Holy Communion row in Greece|agency=Straights Times|date=9 March 2020}}</ref> Some high-profile Greek medical doctors publicly supported the continuation of practicing Holy Communion, drawing criticism from the Greek Association of Hospital Doctors.<ref name=\"Brzozowski Michalopoulos 2020\">{{cite web | last=Brzozowski | first=Alexandra | last2=Michalopoulos | first2=Sarantis | title=Catholics take measures against coronavirus while Greek Orthodox Church 'prays' | website=www.euractiv.com | date=9 March 2020 | url=https://www.euractiv.com/section/health-consumers/news/catholics-take-measures-against-coronavirus-while-greek-orthodox-church-prays/ | access-date=12 March 2020}}</ref> ({{lang-el|\u039f\u03bc\u03bf\u03c3\u03c0\u03bf\u03bd\u03b4\u03af\u03b1 \u0395\u03bd\u03ce\u03c3\u03b5\u03c9\u03bd \u039d\u03bf\u03c3\u03bf\u03ba\u03bf\u03bc\u03b5\u03b9\u03b1\u03ba\u03ce\u03bd \u0393\u03b9\u03b1\u03c4\u03c1\u03ce\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03bf\u03c2}} (OENGE)).\n\nOn 11 March, the prime minister of Greece [[Kyriakos Mitsotakis]], in a nationally televised address, told the public to follow the instructions of doctors and experts, and the Church of Greece to cooperate in enforcing the public health regulations.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tovima.gr/2020/03/11/international/mitsotakis-calls-for-unity-personal-responsibility-cooperation-of-archbishop-to-limit-covid-19/|title=Mitsotakis calls for unity, personal responsibility, cooperation of Archbishop to limit COVID-19|last=Team|first=\u03a4\u03bf\u0392\u0397\u039c\u0391|date=11 March 2020|website=\u0395\u03b9\u03b4\u03ae\u03c3\u03b5\u03b9\u03c2 - \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 - \u03a4\u03bf \u0392\u03ae\u03bc\u03b1 Online|language=el|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref> Two days later, the [[Archbishopric of Athens|Archbishop of Athens and all Greece]] [[Ieronymos II of Athens|Ieronymos]] stated that the Church agreed with and would implement the public health precautionary measures taken by the national authorities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tovima.gr/2020/03/13/society/koronoios-ieronymos-i-ekklisia-mas-oudepote-stathike-apenanti-stin-epistimi-i-epixeirise-na-tin-ypokatastisei/|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2 - \u0399\u03b5\u03c1\u03ce\u03bd\u03c5\u03bc\u03bf\u03c2: \u0397 \u0395\u03ba\u03ba\u03bb\u03b7\u03c3\u03af\u03b1 \u03bc\u03b1\u03c2 \u03bf\u03c5\u03b4\u03ad\u03c0\u03bf\u03c4\u03b5 \u03c3\u03c4\u03ac\u03b8\u03b7\u03ba\u03b5 \u03b1\u03c0\u03ad\u03bd\u03b1\u03bd\u03c4\u03b9 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03c0\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03ae\u03bc\u03b7 \u03ae \u03b5\u03c0\u03b9\u03c7\u03b5\u03af\u03c1\u03b7\u03c3\u03b5 \u03bd\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u03c5\u03c0\u03bf\u03ba\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1\u03c3\u03c4\u03ae\u03c3\u03b5\u03b9|last=Team|first=\u03a4\u03bf\u0392\u0397\u039c\u0391|date=13 March 2020|website=\u0395\u03b9\u03b4\u03ae\u03c3\u03b5\u03b9\u03c2 - \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 - \u03a4\u03bf \u0392\u03ae\u03bc\u03b1 Online|language=el|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 March, after having been briefed by infectious disease spokesman Sotiris Tsiodras, the Church's Standing Synod decided to suspend all public services except Divine Liturgies on Sundays, which were to be held as usual between 7 and 8 o\u2019clock in the morning; weddings and baptisms were suspended, funerals were to be held with only the immediate family present; churches were to remain open for private prayer.<ref name=\"kath\">{{cite news|url= http://www.ekathimerini.com/250716/article/ekathimerini/news/greek-orthodox-church-agrees-to-suspend-daily-services-sacraments-over-coronavirus|title=Greek Orthodox Church agrees to suspend daily services, sacraments over coronavirus|website=Ekatherimini|date=16 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"orthtimessusp\">{{cite web | title=Church of Greece: Weekday services and mysteries are temporarily postponed (upd) | website=OrthodoxTimes | date=9 March 2020 | url=https://orthodoxtimes.com/church-of-greece-everyday-services-and-mysteries-are-temporarily-postponed/ | access-date=3 April 2020}}</ref> Following the Synod's decision, the Greek prime minister announced the government's decision to suspend services in all areas of religious worship of any religion or dogma from 16\u201330 March,<ref name=\"kathimerini\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.kathimerini.gr/1069449/article/epikairothta/politikh/anastellontai-oles-oi-8rhskeytikes-leitoyrgies-me-apofash-ths-kyvernhshs|title=\u0391\u03bd\u03b1\u03c3\u03c4\u03ad\u03bb\u03bb\u03bf\u03bd\u03c4\u03b1\u03b9 \u03cc\u03bb\u03b5\u03c2 \u03bf\u03b9 \u03b8\u03c1\u03b7\u03c3\u03ba\u03b5\u03c5\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ad\u03c2 \u03bb\u03b5\u03b9\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c1\u03b3\u03af\u03b5\u03c2 \u03bc\u03b5 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc\u03c6\u03b1\u03c3\u03b7 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u03ba\u03c5\u03b2\u03ad\u03c1\u03bd\u03b7\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2 {{!}} Kathimerini|website=www.kathimerini.gr|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> effectively suspending Sunday [[Divine Liturgy|Divine Liturgies]] for that period too.<ref name=\"kath2\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ekathimerini.com/250756/article/ekathimerini/news/greek-church-finally-toes-state-line-on-coronavirus|title=Greek Church finally toes state line on coronavirus {{!}} Kathimerini|website=www.ekathimerini.com|language=English|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n\nOn 1 April, the Standing Synod of the Church of Greece issued a statement that urged the faithful to abide by the government's sanitary regulations and to refrain from attending services in churches; it also re-affirmed its stance on the Holy Communion set out in the statement of 9 March 2020 and expressed hope that solemn public celebration of [[Easter]] (Pascha), which would properly be on 19 April, could be performed on the night of 26 May, the eve of the [[Paschal cycle|Leave-Taking (Apodosis) of Pascha]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ecclesia.gr/epikairotita/main_epikairotita_next.asp?id=2993 |title=\u039f\u03b9 \u03b1\u03c0\u03bf\u03c6\u03ac\u03c3\u03b5\u03b9\u03c2 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u0394.\u0399.\u03a3. \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u0395\u03ba\u03ba\u03bb\u03b7\u03c3\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03bf\u03c2 |date=1 April 2020|website=ecclesia.gr|language=el|access-date=3 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cyprustimes.com/iera-synodos-ellados-tha-giortasoyme-pascha-stis-26-ma-oy/ |title=\u0399\u03b5\u03c1\u03ac \u03a3\u03cd\u03bd\u03bf\u03b4\u03bf\u03c2 \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03bf\u03c2: \u0398\u03b1 \u03b3\u03b9\u03bf\u03c1\u03c4\u03ac\u03c3\u03bf\u03c5\u03bc\u03b5 \u03a0\u03ac\u03c3\u03c7\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b9\u03c2 26 \u039c\u03b1\u0390\u03bf\u03c5 |date=1 April 2020|website=cyprustimes.com |language=el|access-date=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Refugees and migrants ===\nOn February 27, prime minister Mitsotakis announced that illegal entry from Turkey would no longer tolerated; as this would be a threat to public health in Greece.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Karaoulanis |first1=Theodore |last2=\u039a\u03b1\u03c1\u03b1\u03bf\u03c5\u03bb\u03ac\u03bd\u03b7\u03c2 |first2=\u0398\u03bf\u03b4\u03c9\u03c1\u03ae\u03c2 |title=\u0391\u03bd\u03ac\u03c3\u03c7\u03b5\u03c3\u03b7 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c3\u03cd\u03bd\u03bf\u03c1\u03b1 \u03c3\u03b5 \u03cc\u03c3\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 \u03c0\u03c1\u03cc\u03c3\u03c6\u03c5\u03b3\u03b5\u03c2 - \u03bc\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03bd\u03ac\u03c3\u03c4\u03b5\u03c2 \u03c0\u03c1\u03bf\u03ad\u03c1\u03c7\u03bf\u03bd\u03c4\u03b1\u03b9 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u0399\u03c1\u03ac\u03bd, \u0391\u03c6\u03b3\u03b1\u03bd\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03ac\u03bd \u03c0\u03c1\u03bf\u03b1\u03bd\u03ae\u03b3\u03b3\u03b5\u03b9\u03bb\u03b5 \u03bf \u03a0\u03c1\u03c9\u03b8\u03c5\u03c0\u03bf\u03c5\u03c1\u03b3\u03cc\u03c2, \u03bb\u03cc\u03b3\u03c9 \u03ba\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03bf\u03cd |url=https://www.euractiv.gr/section/koinoniki-eyropi/news/anaschesi-sta-synora-se-osoys-prosfyges-metanastes-proerchontai-apo-iran-afganistan-proaniggeile-o-prothypoyrgos-logo-koronoioy/ |website=www.euractiv.gr |accessdate=31 March 2020 |language=el |date=27 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Greece's response to coronavirus working, Mitsotakis tells CNN {{!}} Kathimerini |url=http://www.ekathimerini.com/251254/article/ekathimerini/news/greeces-response-to-coronavirus-working-mitsotakis-tells-cnn |website=www.ekathimerini.com |publisher=ekathimarini |accessdate=8 April 2020 |language=English}}</ref> According to various estimates about 150,600 [[displaced person]]s are located in Greece.<ref name=\"Prothero\">{{cite news |last1=Prothero |first1=Mitch |title=In Greece, the government prepares for a crisis that is beyond its capacity to handle |url=https://www.businessinsider.com/coronavirus-greece-prepares-for-crisis-2020-3 |accessdate=26 March 2020 |work=Business Insider |date=2020 |ref=Prothero}}</ref> In the existing camps, doctors, NGOs and refugees considered that measures against the spread of the coronavirus are lacking as people live in overcrowded spaces with little access to proper health services.<ref name=\"AlJazeera\"/><ref name=\"Prothero\"/><ref name=\"Campana\">{{cite news |last1=Campana |first1=Fahrinisa |last2=Patrick |first2=Strickland |title=The Looming Refugee Coronavirus Disaster |url=https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2020/03/refugees-coronavirus-greece.html |accessdate=26 March 2020 |work=Slate |date=2020 |ref=Campana}}</ref> On March 24, 21 international human rights organizations active in Greece including [[Amnesty International]], the [[Human Rights Watch]] and [[ActionAid]] published an open call to the Greek government to take immediate measures to prevent the spread of COVID-19 in the Reception and Identification Centres, where refugees live. The conditions of the centres were criticised as deplorable and dangerous to both the refugees and public health.<ref name=\"HRW\">{{cite web |title=Greece: Move Asylum Seekers, Migrants to Safety |url=https://www.hrw.org/news/2020/03/24/greece-move-asylum-seekers-migrants-safety |website=HRW |accessdate=27 March 2020 |ref=HRW}}</ref> [[M\u00e9decins Sans Fronti\u00e8res]] which has a clinic near the Moria camp declared that the numbers in the camps had reached levels such that they could not handle an outbreak of infection within the camp. The government further announced that movement of refugees outside the camps would be restricted as facilities are prepared for confirmed cases,<ref name=\"Fotiadis\">{{cite news |last1=Fotiadis |first1=Apostolos |title=Greece Ramps up Restrictions but Faces Criticism over Coronavirus Response |url=https://balkaninsight.com/2020/03/25/greece-ramps-up-restrictions-but-faces-criticism-over-coronavirus-response/ |accessdate=27 March 2020 |publisher=Balkan Insight |date=2020 |ref=Fotiadis}}</ref> and that it would only allow small goups of refugees and migrants to temporarily exit the camps to obtain basic supplies.<ref name=\"AlJazeera\">{{cite news |title=Greece curbs refugee movement in camps over coronavirus fears |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/greece-curbs-refugee-movement-camps-coronavirus-fears-200318162208279.html |accessdate=26 March 2020 |work=Al Jazeera |date=2020 |ref=AlJazeera}}</ref>\n\nOn March 28, the Turkish interior minister announced that 5,800 refugees and migrants that had unsuccessfully attempted to cross the Greek-Turkish border had been relocated to Turkish cities due to the coronavirus pandemic. He also announced that as soon as the pandemic subsided these people would be returned to the border.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u03a4\u03bf\u03cd\u03c1\u03ba\u03bf\u03c2 \u03a5\u03a0\u0395\u03a3: \u039c\u03b5\u03c4\u03ac \u03c4\u03b7 \u03bb\u03ae\u03be\u03b7 \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u03ba\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03bf\u03cd \u03c0\u03c1\u03cc\u03c3\u03c6\u03c5\u03b3\u03b5\u03c2 \u03bc\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03bd\u03ac\u03c3\u03c4\u03b5\u03c2 \u03be\u03b1\u03bd\u03ac \u03c3\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c3\u03cd\u03bd\u03bf\u03c1\u03b1 |url=https://www.sofokleousin.gr/tourkos-ypes-meta-ti-liksi-tou-koronoiou-prosfyges-metanastes-ksa |website=www.sofokleousin.gr |accessdate=31 March 2020 |language=el}}</ref>\n\nOn March 31, it was reported that two individuals were infected in the [[Vathy, Euboea#Ritsona|Ritsona]] refugee camp in Central Greece.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ethnos.gr/ellada/97339_thetiko-ston-koronoio-zeygari-apo-tin-afriki-sto-hot-pot-tis-ritsonas|title=\u0398\u03b5\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc \u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u03ba\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc \u03b6\u03b5\u03c5\u03b3\u03ac\u03c1\u03b9 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0391\u03c6\u03c1\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae \u03c3\u03c4\u03bf hot pot \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u03a1\u03b9\u03c4\u03c3\u03ce\u03bd\u03b1\u03c2|trans-title=Positive to coronavirus, a couple from Africa ...|date=31 March 2020|website=\u0388\u03b8\u03bd\u03bf\u03c2}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.skai.gr/news/ygeia/poedin-thetiki-ston-koronoio-metanastria-apo-ti-ritsona-pou-gennise-sto-aleksandra|title=\u03a0\u039f\u0395\u0394\u0397\u039d: \u0398\u03b5\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae \u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u03ba\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc \u03bc\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03bd\u03ac\u03c3\u03c4\u03c1\u03b9\u03b1 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03b7 \u03a1\u03b9\u03c4\u03c3\u03ce\u03bd\u03b1 \u03c0\u03bf\u03c5 \u03b3\u03ad\u03bd\u03bd\u03b7\u03c3\u03b5 \u03c3\u03c4\u03bf \u0391\u03bb\u03b5\u03be\u03ac\u03bd\u03b4\u03c1\u03b1|trans-title=Positive to coronavirus, a Ritsona woman immigrant who gave birth in Alexandra Hospital|website=\u03a3\u039a\u0391\u03aa}}</ref>\n\nGreek officials have stated that the reason for segregating new arrivals of refugees from Turkey, is due to concerns that Turkey may deliberately send infected refugees and migrants so as to spread the virus through the camps.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.protothema.gr/politics/article/992012/koronoios-surigos-fovomaste-oti-i-tourkia-borei-na-steilei-epitides-sta-nisia-mas-foreis-tou-iou/|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2 - \u03a3\u03c5\u03c1\u03af\u03b3\u03bf\u03c2: \u00ab\u03a6\u03bf\u03b2\u03cc\u03bc\u03b1\u03c3\u03c4\u03b5 \u03cc\u03c4\u03b9 \u03b7 \u03a4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c1\u03ba\u03af\u03b1 \u03bc\u03c0\u03bf\u03c1\u03b5\u03af \u03bd\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b5\u03af\u03bb\u03b5\u03b9 \u03b5\u03c0\u03af\u03c4\u03b7\u03b4\u03b5\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b1 \u03bd\u03b7\u03c3\u03b9\u03ac \u03bc\u03b1\u03c2 \u03c6\u03bf\u03c1\u03b5\u03af\u03c2 \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u03b9\u03bf\u03cd\u00bb|date=3 April 2020|website=ProtoThema}}</ref><ref>https://www.ethnos.gr/politiki/97996_syrigos-i-toyrkia-mporei-na-mas-steilei-epitides-foreis-toy-koronoioy</ref><ref>https://www.dimokratiki.gr/03-04-2020/aggelos-syrigos-fovamai-min-steiloyn-epitides-oi-toyrkoi-metanastes-foreis-toy-koronoioy-sta-nisia/</ref><ref>https://www.tribune.gr/politics/news/article/655733/aggelos-syrigos-prepei-na-proetoimazomaste-gia-thermo-epeisodio.html</ref> It was reported that Turkish coastguard were sighted near boats with illegal immigrants off the Greek islands, keeping safety distance and wearing medical protective suits.<ref>[https://greekcitytimes.com/2020/04/04/biological-warfare-turkey-attempts-to-send-coronavirus-infected-migrants-to-greece/ \"Biological warfare? Turkey attempts to send coronavirus infected migrants to Greece\", Greek City Times, April 6, 2020.]</ref>\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://covid19.gov.gr/covid19-live-analytics/]  - Covid19 Live Analytics\n* [https://eody.gov.gr/ \u0391\u03c1\u03c7\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae] - Official website of the Greek [[National Public Health Organization (Greece)|National Public Health Organization]] with information regarding the progress of the pandemic in the country\n* [https://lab.imedd.org/covid19/ COVID\u201419] \u2013 map with various updated statistics\n* [http://geochoros.survey.ntua.gr/coronavirus/ CoVID-GEO] - geographical analysis and mapping of Coronavirus COVID-19 related world data through a web-based platform developed by the GeoCHOROS Geospatial Analysis and Research Group at the National Technical University of Athens, Greece\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n{{Portal bar|COVID-19|Greece|Medicine|Viruses}}\n\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Greece]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Greece]]\n[[Category:February 2020 events in Europe]]\n[[Category:2020 in Greece]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|Greece]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in Europe]]\n", "text_old": "{{Current disaster|event=pandemic|date=January 2020}} \n{{EngvarB|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Greece}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Greece\n| map1            = COVID-19 Outbreak Cases in Greece per regional unit (prefecture).svg\n| legend1         = Map of the COVID-19 outbreak in Greece {{as of|2020|March|29|lc=y}}.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://eody.gov.gr/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/covid-gr-daily-report-29-03-20.pdf|title=EODY daily report 29 March 2020}}</ref>\n{{legend|#FCEED3|Confirmed 1\u20144}}\n{{legend|#F2A88D|Confirmed 5\u20149}}\n{{legend|#E36654|Confirmed 10\u201449}}\n{{legend|#E5354B|Confirmed 50\u201499}}\n{{legend|#87353F|Confirmed 100\u2014199}}\n{{legend|#630606|Confirmed \u2265200}}\n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Greece]]\n| first_case      = [[Thessaloniki]]\n| arrival_date    = 26 February 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=02|day1=26|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], [[China]]\n| recovery_cases  = 273<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://eody.gov.gr/0408_briefing_covid19/|title=\u0395\u03bd\u03b7\u03bc\u03ad\u03c1\u03c9\u03c3\u03b7 \u03b4\u03b9\u03b1\u03c0\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03b5\u03c5\u03bc\u03ad\u03bd\u03c9\u03bd \u03c3\u03c5\u03bd\u03c4\u03b1\u03ba\u03c4\u03ce\u03bd \u03c5\u03b3\u03b5\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 08-04-2020|last=|first=|date=2020-04-08|website=National Public Health Organization|language=el|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n| deaths          = 90<ref>{{cite news |title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03b1\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u03a3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 89 \u03bf\u03b9 \u03bd\u03b5\u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03af \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1 \u2013 \u03a0\u03ad\u03b8\u03b1\u03bd\u03b5 67\u03c7\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03b7 \u03c3\u03c4\u03bf \u00ab\u0391\u03c3\u03ba\u03bb\u03b7\u03c0\u03b9\u03b5\u03af\u03bf\u00bb|url=https://www.in.gr/2020/04/10/greece/koronaios-stous-89-oi-nekroi-stin-ellada-pethane-67xroni-sto-asklipieio/ |accessdate=10 April 2020 |work=in.gr |date=9 April 2020 |language=el}}</ref>\n| confirmed_cases = 2011\n| total_ili       = \n| date            = {{as of|2020|April|10}}\n| website         = {{URL|https://www.moh.gov.gr}}\n}}\n\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] first appeared in [[Greece]] on 26 February 2020. Initial cases related to people who had travelled to Italy, as well as a group of pilgrims who had travelled to [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Israel|Israel]] and [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Egypt|Egypt]] and their contacts.\n\n{{As of|2020|04|9|df=UK}}, there have been 1955 confirmed cases and 86 deaths. Health authorities recommend travellers who have returned from affected areas or people who have been in contact with such travellers to stay home for a minimum of 14 days. It may take 2\u201314 days for symptoms to appear after initial exposure to the virus. Thirteen reporting hospitals have been designated to deal with cases. The main affected areas are [[Elis (regional unit)|Ilia]] and [[Attica (region)|Attica]].\n\nFollowing the confirmation of the first three cases in Greece, on 27 February all [[carnival]] events in the country were cancelled, and by 10 March a total of 89 cases had been confirmed in the country, mainly related to people who had travelled to Italy and a group of pilgrims who had travelled to Israel and Egypt, as well as their contacts. Health and state authorities issued precautionary guidelines and recommendations, while measures up to that point were taken locally and included the closure of schools and the suspension of cultural events in the affected areas (particularly [[Elis (regional unit)|Ilia]], [[Achaea]] and [[Zakynthos]]). However, on 10 March, due to the outbreak of the virus in different parts of the country and failure by many to comply with the restrictive measures, the government decided to suspend the operation of educational institutions of all levels nationwide and then, on 13 March, to close down all cafes, bars, museums, shopping centres, sports facilities and restaurants in the country. On 16 March, all retail shops were also closed, two villages in Kozani were quarantined, and all services in all areas of religious worship of any religion or dogma were suspended. On 18 and 19 March, the government announced a series of measures of more than 10 billion euros to support the economy, businesses and employees.\n\nOn 22 March, the Greek authorities announced restrictions on all non-essential movement throughout the country, starting from 6 a.m on 23 March. Since that date, movement outside the house is permitted only for seven categories of reasons: i) moving to or from one's workplace during work hours, ii) going to the pharmacy or visiting a doctor iii) going to a food store iv) going to the bank for services not possible online, v) assisting a person in need of help vi) going to a major ritual (funeral, marriage, baptism) or movement, for divorced parents, which is essential for contact with their children, and vii) moving outdoors, near one's home, for exercising or taking one's pet out, individually or in pairs. Citizens leaving their home are required to carry their police ID or passport, as well as a signed attestation in which the purpose or category of travel is stated. The [[Hellenic Police]], the [[Municipal Police (Greece)|Municipal Police]], the [[Hellenic Coast Guard]] and the National Transparency Authority are empowered to enforce the restrictions and can issue fines for each offense. On 4 April these restrictions were extended until 27 April. \n\nThe measures put in place in Greece are some of the most proactive and strict in Europe and have been hailed internationally for slowing the spread of the disease and keeping the number of deaths among the lowest on the continent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2020-04-10/greece-handled-coronavirus-crisis-better-than-italy-and-spain|title=Greece Shows How to Handle the Crisis|last=Giugliano|first=Ferdinando|date=10 April 2020|via=Bloomberg.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/05/world/europe/scientists-coronavirus-heroes.html|title=The Rising Heroes of the Coronavirus Era? Nations\u2019 Top Scientists|last=Stevis-Gridneff|first=Matina|date=5 April 2020|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref><ref name=\"lefigaro\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.lefigaro.fr/international/l-infectiologue-sotirios-tsiodras-nouvelle-coqueluche-des-grecs-20200320|title=L\u2019infectiologue Sotirios Tsiodras, nouvelle coqueluche des Grecs|last=Kefalas|first=Alexia|date=20 March 2020|website=Le Figaro.fr|language=French}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2020-04-07/stocks-rally-suggests-turning-point-in-coronavirus-fight|title=Stocks Rally Suggests Turning Point In Coronavirus Fight|last=|first=|date=|website=www.bloomberg.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/greeks-rein-in-rebellious-streak-as-draconian-measures-earn-them-a-reprieve-tznc0bn6s|title=Greeks rein in rebellious streak as draconian measures earn them a reprieve|last=Athens|first=Anthee Carassava|via=www.thetimes.co.uk}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ethnos.gr/kosmos/95931_ellinas-giatros-sto-mpermigham-protypo-i-ellada-i-bretania-se-heiroteri-thesi-apo-tin|title=Greek Doctor at Bermigham: Greece is exemplar, Britain in worse position than Italy (Original: \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03b7\u03bd\u03b1\u03c2 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1\u03c4\u03c1\u03cc\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03bf \u039c\u03c0\u03ad\u03c1\u03bc\u03b9\u03b3\u03c7\u03b1\u03bc: \u03a0\u03c1\u03cc\u03c4\u03c5\u03c0\u03bf \u03b7 \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1, \u03b7 \u0392\u03c1\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03bd\u03af\u03b1 \u03c3\u03b5 \u03c7\u03b5\u03b9\u03c1\u03cc\u03c4\u03b5\u03c1\u03b7 \u03b8\u03ad\u03c3\u03b7 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0399\u03c4\u03b1\u03bb\u03af\u03b1)|date=24 March 2020|website=\u0388\u03b8\u03bd\u03bf\u03c2}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n== Timeline ==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Greece medical cases chart}}\n\n=== February 2020 ===\n* On 26 February, the first case in Greece was confirmed. A 38-year-old woman from [[Thessaloniki]], who had recently visited [[Milan]], [[northern Italy|\u039dorthern Italy]], tested positive and was admitted to [[AHEPA University Hospital]]. Her family, as well as those who came into contact with her, voluntarily isolated themselves.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-greece-idUSKCN20K1IA|title=Greece confirms first coronavirus case|date=26 February 2020|work=Reuters|access-date=26 February 2020|language=en}}</ref>\n* On 27 February, two new cases in Greece were confirmed. The woman's nine-year-old child tested positive and was admitted to the same hospital as her mother.<ref name=\":17\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.iefimerida.gr/ellada/koronoios-deytero-thetiko-kroysma-stin-ellada-paidi-38hronis|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u0394\u03b5\u03cd\u03c4\u03b5\u03c1\u03bf \u03b8\u03b5\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1 -\u03a4\u03bf \u03c0\u03b1\u03b9\u03b4\u03af \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 38\u03c7\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03b7\u03c2 {{!}} \u0395\u039b\u039b\u0391\u0394\u0391|date=27 February 2020|website=iefimerida.gr|language=el|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> Additionally, a forty-year-old woman who had travelled to Italy, also tested positive and was admitted to Attikon University General Hospital.<ref name=\":8\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.iefimerida.gr/ellada/koronoios-athina-trito-kroysma-stin-ellada-akyronontai-ola-ta-karnabalia|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u03a3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0391\u03b8\u03ae\u03bd\u03b1 \u03c4\u03bf \u03c4\u03c1\u03af\u03c4\u03bf \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1 -\u0391\u03ba\u03c5\u03c1\u03ce\u03bd\u03bf\u03bd\u03c4\u03b1\u03b9 \u03cc\u03bb\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03ba\u03b1\u03c1\u03bd\u03b1\u03b2\u03ac\u03bb\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u03c7\u03ce\u03c1\u03b1 {{!}} \u0395\u039b\u039b\u0391\u0394\u0391|last=IEFIMERIDA.GR|first=NEWSROOM|date=27 February 2020|website=iefimerida.gr|language=el|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":7\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.ant1news.gr/ygeia-periballon/article/561073/koronoios-tria-kroysmata-stin-ellada-akyronontai-oi-ekdiloseis-gia-to-karnabali-se-oli-ti-xora|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u03c4\u03c1\u03af\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1 - \u0391\u03ba\u03c5\u03c1\u03ce\u03bd\u03bf\u03bd\u03c4\u03b1\u03b9 \u03bf\u03b9 \u03b5\u03ba\u03b4\u03b7\u03bb\u03ce\u03c3\u03b5\u03b9\u03c2 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c4\u03bf \u039a\u03b1\u03c1\u03bd\u03b1\u03b2\u03ac\u03bb\u03b9 \u03c3\u03b5 \u03cc\u03bb\u03b7 \u03c4\u03b7 \u03c7\u03ce\u03c1\u03b1|website=antenna.gr|language=el|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-greece-idUSKCN20L1F3|title=Greece reports two new coronavirus cases, cancels carnival|date=27 February 2020|work=Reuters|access-date=27 February 2020|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news247.gr/koinonia/koronoios-stin-athina-mia-gynaika-to-proto-kroysma.7592170.html|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0391\u03b8\u03ae\u03bd\u03b1: \u0393\u03c5\u03bd\u03b1\u03af\u03ba\u03b1, \u03c3\u03cd\u03b6\u03c5\u03b3\u03bf\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b5\u03bb\u03ad\u03c7\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 \u03bd\u03b1\u03c5\u03c4\u03b9\u03bb\u03b9\u03b1\u03ba\u03ae\u03c2 \u03c4\u03bf \u03c0\u03c1\u03ce\u03c4\u03bf \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1 - \u039d\u03bf\u03c3\u03b7\u03bb\u03b5\u03cd\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03b9 \u03c3\u03c4\u03bf \u0391\u03c4\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc|website=www.news247.gr|language=el|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref> Following the confirmation of the second and third cases in Greece, it was announced that the 105th Primary School of Thessaloniki, where the first patient's daughter went to school, would close for fourteen days. The Minister of Health, [[Vasilis Kikilias]], announced that all carnival events were cancelled throughout Greece.<ref name=\":7\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/209034/o-koronaios-eftase-stin-ellada-proto-epivevaiomeno-kroysma-sti-thessaloniki|title=\u039f \u03ba\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03b1\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2 \u03ad\u03c6\u03c4\u03b1\u03c3\u03b5 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1: \u03a0\u03c1\u03ce\u03c4\u03bf \u03b5\u03c0\u03b9\u03b2\u03b5\u03b2\u03b1\u03b9\u03c9\u03bc\u03ad\u03bd\u03bf \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u0398\u03b5\u03c3\u03c3\u03b1\u03bb\u03bf\u03bd\u03af\u03ba\u03b7|last=Newsroom|date=26 February 2020|website=CNN.gr|language=el|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":8\" />\n* On 28 February, the fourth case in Greece was confirmed. A 36-year-old woman from [[Athens]] who had recently travelled to Italy tested positive and was admitted to the Attikon University General Hospital.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.news247.gr/koinonia/koronoios-tetarto-kroysma-gynaika-36-eton-stin-athina.7592735.html|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u03a4\u03ad\u03c4\u03b1\u03c1\u03c4\u03bf \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1 - \u039a\u03b1\u03b8\u03b7\u03b3\u03ae\u03c4\u03c1\u03b9\u03b1 36 \u03b5\u03c4\u03ce\u03bd \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0391\u03b8\u03ae\u03bd\u03b1|date=28 February 2020|work=News247|access-date=28 February 2020|language=el}}</ref><ref name=\":17\" /> Eight state schools were closed as a precautionary measure in [[Attica]] to prevent the spread of the virus, and all educational travel abroad sponsored by Greek schools was halted.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.tornosnews.gr/en/greek-news/society/39157-4-confirmed-coronavirus-cases-in-greece-and-8-schools-closed-in-attica.html|title=4 confirmed coronavirus cases in Greece and 8 schools closed in Attica|agency=Tornos News|date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n* On 29 February, three new cases in Greece were confirmed. A friend of the 38-year-old woman who was the first case in Greece, was admitted to the AHEPA University Hospital.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.iefimerida.gr/ellada/koronoios-pempto-kroysma-stin-ellada|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u03a0\u03ad\u03bc\u03c0\u03c4\u03bf \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1|date=29 February 2020|work=iefimerida|access-date=29 February 2020|language=el}}</ref> Additionally, two more people in Athens were admitted to the General Hospital Sotiria, bringing the country total to seven confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0391\u03bd\u03b5\u03b2\u03b1\u03af\u03bd\u03b5\u03b9 \u03bf \u03b1\u03c1\u03b9\u03b8\u03bc\u03cc\u03c2: \u0395\u03c0\u03c4\u03ac \u03c4\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u03ba\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03b1\u03ca\u03bf\u03cd \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1 |url=https://www.gazzetta.gr/plus/koinwnia/article/1451205/anevainei-o-arithmos-epta-ta-kroysmata-toy-koronaioy-stin-ellada |website=www.gazzetta.gr |language=el}}</ref>\n\n=== March 2020 ===\n\n* On 4 March, two new cases were confirmed in Greece. A middle-aged man in close contact with the fifth confirmed case, tested positive and was put in solitary confinement at AHEPA University Hospital.<ref>{{cite Web |title=\u039f\u03b3\u03b4\u03bf\u03bf \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1 \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u03b9\u03bf\u03cd \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1|url=https://www.euro2day.gr/news/highlights/article/2010891/ogdoo-kroysma-toy-ioy-sthn-ellada.html|website=www.euro2day.gr|language=el}}</ref> Additionally, a man who had travelled to Israel and Egypt, was admitted to the [[General University Hospital of Patras]], bringing the country total to nine confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite Web |title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03b1\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u0388\u03bd\u03b1\u03c4\u03bf \u03b5\u03c0\u03b9\u03b2\u03b5\u03b2\u03b1\u03b9\u03c9\u03bc\u03ad\u03bd\u03bf \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u03a0\u03ac\u03c4\u03c1\u03b1|url=https://www.onmed.gr/ygeia-eidhseis/story/382322/koronoios-stin-patra-to-enato-kroysma|website=www.onmed.gr|date=4 March 2020|language=el}}</ref>\n* On 5 March, 22 new cases were confirmed in Greece. The 66-year-old wife, who was the ninth case in Greece, tested positive and was admitted to the same hospital as her husband.<ref>{{cite Web|url=https://www.news247.gr/koinonia/koronoios-stin-patra-kai-to-dekato-kroysma.7596006.amp.html|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03bf\u03c2: \u03a3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u03a0\u03ac\u03c4\u03c1\u03b1 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03c4\u03bf \u03b4\u03ad\u03ba\u03b1\u03c4\u03bf \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1 - \u03a0\u03c1\u03cc\u03ba\u03b5\u03b9\u03c4\u03b1\u03b9 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b7 \u03c3\u03cd\u03b6\u03c5\u03b3\u03bf \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 66\u03c7\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03c5|website=www.news247.gr|language=el}}</ref> 21 of their fellow travellers also tested positive, bringing the country total to 31 cases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/210074/koronoios-stin-ellada-sta-31-ta-kroysmata-toy-ioy-21-nea|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1: \u03a3\u03c4\u03b1 31 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u03b9\u03bf\u03cd - 21 \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1|last=Newsroom|date=5 March 2020|website=CNN.gr|language=el|access-date=5 March 2020}}</ref>\n* On 6 March, 14 new cases were confirmed in Greece. Eleven members of the Israel-Egypt travel group, as well as three people who afterwards came in contact with them, tested positive, bringing the country total to 45 confirmed cases. Schools, universities, theaters and cinemas were closed until 22 March in three of the affected areas ([[Achaia]], [[Ileia]] and [[Zakynthos]]).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newsit.gr/ellada/koronoios-14-akoma-krousmata-stin-ellad/2988717/|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: 14 \u03b1\u03ba\u03cc\u03bc\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1!|date=6 March 2020|website=NewsIt|language=el|access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref>\n* On 7 March, 21 new cases were confirmed in Greece. Thirteen people in Achaia and Ileia, seven in Attica and one in Euboea tested positive, bringing the country total to 66 confirmed cases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kathimerini.gr/1068124/article/epikairothta/ellada/korwnoios-21-nea-kroysmata---stoys-66-synolika-oi-as8eneis|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: 21 \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 - \u03a3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 66 \u03c3\u03c5\u03bd\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac \u03bf\u03b9 \u03b1\u03c3\u03b8\u03b5\u03bd\u03b5\u03af\u03c2|date=7 March 2020|website=kathimerini|language=el|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n* On 8 March, seven new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the country total to 73.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.in.gr/2020/03/08/greece/koronaios-73-krousmata-kekleismenon-ton-thyron-oi-athlitikes-ekdiloseis/|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03b1\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2 : 73 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 - \u039a\u03b5\u03ba\u03bb\u03b5\u03b9\u03c3\u03bc\u03ad\u03bd\u03c9\u03bd \u03c4\u03c9\u03bd \u03b8\u03c5\u03c1\u03ce\u03bd \u03bf\u03b9 \u03b1\u03b8\u03bb\u03b7\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ad\u03c2 \u03b5\u03ba\u03b4\u03b7\u03bb\u03ce\u03c3\u03b5\u03b9\u03c2|last=|website=in.gr|language=el|accessdate=8 March 2020|date=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n* On 9 March, eleven new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the country total to 84.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.iefimerida.gr/ellada/koronoios-live-i-enimerosi-tsiodra-09-03-2020|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: 11 \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 -\u039c\u03b5\u03af\u03bd\u03b5\u03c4\u03b5 \u03c3\u03c0\u03af\u03c4\u03b9 \u03c3\u03b1\u03c2, \u03bb\u03ad\u03b5\u03b9 \u03bf \u039a\u03b9\u03ba\u03af\u03bb\u03b9\u03b1\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b9\u03c2 \u03b5\u03c5\u03c0\u03b1\u03b8\u03b5\u03af\u03c2 \u03bf\u03bc\u03ac\u03b4\u03b5\u03c2|last=|first=|website=iefimerida.gr|publisher=|language=el|archiveurl=|archivedate=|accessdate=9 March 2020|date=9 March 2020}}</ref> Among those cases was the first one to be reported in [[Lesbos]], raising fears that the virus could spread to the island's tightly packed refugee camps.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.sbs.com.au/news/first-coronavirus-case-on-greek-island-filled-with-migrants|title=First coronavirus case on Greek island filled with migrants|date=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n* On 10 March, five new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the country total to 89.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/210621/koronoios-stin-ellada-anakoinothikan-pente-nea-kroysmata|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1: \u0391\u03bd\u03b1\u03ba\u03bf\u03b9\u03bd\u03ce\u03b8\u03b7\u03ba\u03b1\u03bd \u03c0\u03ad\u03bd\u03c4\u03b5 \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1|date=10 March 2020|website=cnn.gr|language=el|access-date=19 March 2020}}</ref> [[Evangelos Marinakis]], the owner of the football clubs [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]] in Greece and [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] in [[England]], informed the public via social media that he had contracted the virus, and urged all to follow the orders of health professionals.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://greekcitytimes.com/2020/03/10/olympiacos-vangelis-marinakis-diagnosed-with-coronavirus/|title=Olympiacos: Vangelis Marinakis diagnosed with coronavirus|agency=Greek City Times|date=10 March 2020}}</ref> Health Minister Vasilis Kikilias announced the closure of all educational institutions for 14 days.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/210695/koronoios-kleinoyn-ola-ta-sxoleia-tis-xoras/|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u039a\u03bb\u03b5\u03af\u03bd\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd \u03cc\u03bb\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c7\u03bf\u03bb\u03b5\u03af\u03b1 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03c0\u03b1\u03bd\u03b5\u03c0\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03ae\u03bc\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u03c7\u03ce\u03c1\u03b1\u03c2|agency=CNN.gr|date=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n* On 11 March, ten new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the country total to 99. The 66-year-old man hospitalised in Rio is diagnosed with multi organ dysfunction syndrome.<ref>[https://www.iefimerida.gr/ellada/koronoios-99-kroysmata-stin-ellada-akyronontai-oi-parelaseis-diaggelma-mitsotaki-stis-1900 \u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: 99 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1 -\u0391\u03ba\u03c5\u03c1\u03ce\u03bd\u03bf\u03bd\u03c4\u03b1\u03b9 \u03bf\u03b9 \u03c0\u03b1\u03c1\u03b5\u03bb\u03ac\u03c3\u03b5\u03b9\u03c2] ''Coronavirus: 99 cases in Greece - Parades canceled'', ''www.iefimerida.gr'', accessed 12 March 2020</ref>\n* On 12 March, 18 new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the country total to 117.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.skai.gr/index.php/news/greece/koronoios-18-nea-krousmata-stin-ellada-117-synolika | title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: 18 \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1 - 117 \u03c3\u03c5\u03bd\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac - \u0394\u03ad\u03ba\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b1 \"\u03bf\u03c1\u03c6\u03b1\u03bd\u03ac\"}}</ref> The first two reported cases in Greece, a mother and her child, were released from the hospital, having fully recovered.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ekathimerini.com/250555/article/ekathimerini/news/greek-coronavirus-cases-rise-to-117-two-released-from-hospital|title=Greek coronavirus cases rise to 117; two released from hospital|date=12 March 2020|website=ekathimerini-com|language=en|access-date=12 March 2020}}</ref> The 66-year-old patient in Rio died as a result of the virus, which was the first virus-related death in Greece.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.moh.gov.gr/articles/ministry/grafeio-typoy/press-releases/6839-anakoinwsh-toy-prwtoy-thanatoy-apo-ton-sars-cov-2|title=\u0391\u03bd\u03b1\u03ba\u03bf\u03af\u03bd\u03c9\u03c3\u03b7 \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u03c0\u03c1\u03ce\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u03b8\u03b1\u03bd\u03ac\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03bf\u03bd SARS-CoV-2|agency=Ministry of Health|date=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n* On 13 March, 73 new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the country total to 190.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.skai.gr/news/greece/koronoios-190-ta-krousmata-stin-ellada-5-diasolinomenoi-11-ta-orfana|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: 190 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1 - 5 \u03b4\u03b9\u03b1\u03c3\u03c9\u03bb\u03b7\u03bd\u03c9\u03bc\u03ad\u03bd\u03bf\u03b9 - 11 \u03c4\u03b1 \"\u03bf\u03c1\u03c6\u03b1\u03bd\u03ac\"|website=\u03a3\u039a\u0391\u03aa|language=el|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref> [[Katerina Sakellaropoulou]] was sworn in [[President of Greece]] in the [[Hellenic Parliament]] and became the first woman to hold the office, succeeding [[Prokopis Pavlopoulos]]. Sakellaropoulou suspended the protocol ceremony for the inauguration scheduled for Saturday 14 and no handshakes were allowed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/greeces-female-president-sworn-69576512|title=Greece's first female president is sworn in|website=ABC News|language=en|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usnews.com/news/world/articles/2020-03-13/greece-swears-in-first-female-president-no-handshakes-amid-coronavirus|title=Greece Swears in First Female President, No Handshakes Amid Coronavirus|website=US News|language=en|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref>\n* On 14 March, 38 new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the country total to 228, while six more were released from hospitals, bringing the recovered total to eight.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/211239/koronoios-38-nea-kroysmata-ta-perissotera-stin-athina|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\